<div class="xar-mod-head"><span class="xar-mod-title"><xar:mlstring>Highlight Administration</xar:mlstring></span></div>
<div class="xar-mod-body"><h2><xar:mlstring>Overview</xar:mlstring></h2>
<div style="margin: auto;"><xar:template file="admin-menu" type="module" />

    <img src="#xarTplGetImage('admin.gif')#" alt="#xarML('official icon')#" width="96" height="96" class="xar-module-icon" />

    <h3><xar:mlstring>What is it?</xar:mlstring></h3>

    <p>
        <xar:mlstring>The Highlight module is a syntax highlighting hook.  Highlighting is accomplished by the <a href="http://qbnz.com/highlighter/">GeSHi</a> utility.</xar:mlstring>
    </p>

    <h3><xar:mlstring>How to use it?</xar:mlstring></h3>

    <p>
    <xar:ml>
        <xar:mlstring>First, make sure to <a href="#(1)">enable the Highlight hook</a> wherever needed.</xar:mlstring>
        <xar:mlvar>#xarModURL('modules', 'admin', 'hooks', array('hook' => 'highlight'))#</xar:mlvar>
    </xar:ml>
    </p>

    <p>
    <xar:ml>
        <xar:mlstring>The Highlight hook will <b>only</b> transform portions of your content labeled with the attribute specified in <a href="#(1)">Modify Config</a>. The attribute's value identifies the coding language.  See the <a href="#(3)">Languages page</a> for a list of what is suppoted.  Your attribute name is currently set to <code>#(2)</code>.  Let's say you want to highlight some PHP code.  The segment in your article must be labeled with <code>#(2)="php"</code>, as follows:</xar:mlstring>
        <xar:mlvar>#xarModURL('highlight', 'admin', 'modifyconfig')#</xar:mlvar>
        <xar:mlvar>#$string#</xar:mlvar>
        <xar:mlvar>#xarModURL('highlight', 'admin', 'languages')#</xar:mlvar>
    </xar:ml>
    </p>

   <pre>#$htmlsample#</pre>

       <p>
              <xar:mlstring>When processed, your content will be rendered like:</xar:mlstring>
       </p>

       <blockquote>
            #$transformsample#
       </blockquote>
<br />

    <h3><xar:mlstring>Included Blocks</xar:mlstring></h3>

    <p>
        <xar:mlstring>The Highlight module has no blocks included at this time.</xar:mlstring>
    </p>

    <h3><xar:mlstring>Included Hooks</xar:mlstring></h3>

    <ul>
        <li><xar:mlstring>transform -- Performs syntax highlighting on embedded programming code</xar:mlstring></li>
    </ul>

